Package org.odpi.openmetadata.frameworks.opensurvey.ffdc

Enum Class OSFAuditCode

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<OSFAuditCode>
org.odpi.openmetadata.frameworks.opensurvey.ffdc.OSFAuditCode
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<OSFAuditCode>, Constable, AuditLogMessageSet
public enum OSFAuditCode extends Enum<OSFAuditCode> implements AuditLogMessageSet
The OSFAuditCode is used to define the message content for the Audit Log. The 5 fields in the enum are:
  • Log Message Identifier - to uniquely identify the message
  • Severity - is this an event, decision, action, error or exception
  • Log Message Text - includes placeholder to allow additional values to be captured
  • Additional Information - further parameters and data relating to the audit message (optional)
  • SystemAction - describes the result of the situation
  • UserAction - describes how a user should correct the situation
